INSERT INTO `blogposts` (`id`, `post_author`, `post_date`, `post_content`, `post_title`, `post_category`, `post_karma`, `post_uri`, `changed`, `post_comment_mode`, `post_status`) VALUES (1677,'3','2004-03-18 09:10:48','After finally getting Chora to work with subversion (you need horde, chora and framework from <a href=\"http://horde.org\">horde\'s</a> CVS HEAD and the installation of horde seems to be somewhat easier today than it was last time I did it), I decided to move to <a href=\"http://subversion.tigris.org\">subversion</a> instead of CVS for my new projects.\nWhile initial installation of subversion was not a big deal (apt-get install subversion), it was a real PITA to get <a href=\"http://svnbook.red-bean.com/book/ch06s04.html#svn-ch-6-sect-4.4.2\">directory based user authentication</a> with the help of mod_authz_svn properly working. First, it did not work together with SVNParentPath, which was fixed\nin 1.0.1. apt-get install -t unstable subversion. Now it did somehow work, but didn\'t record the username of commiters. Not really an acceptable solution. Further trying, testing, tweaking. No. Doesn\'t work. So I <a href=\"http://subversion.tigris.org/servlets/ReadMsg?list=users&amp;msgNo=8065\">posted</a> to the users-list of subversion about my\nproblem. <a href=\"http://subversion.tigris.org/servlets/ReadMsg?list=users&amp;msgNo=8092\">Prompt answer</a>. Known Problem. <a href=\"http://subversion.tigris.org/issues/show_bug.cgi?id=1786\">Fixed in the trunk</a>. So I got the trunk, still doesn\'t work. No authentication at all needed now for writing. Then I tried the specific revision (r9077)\nmentioned in the bug report. And yes it worked. Finally ;)<br />\n<br />\nNow everything is together for finally using subversion for serious work. You can look at it with Chora at <a href=\"http://cvs.bitflux.ch\">http://cvs.bitflux.ch/</a>. The repository itself can be found at <a href=\"http://svn.bitflux.ch/repos/public/\">http://svn.bitflux.ch/repos/public</a><br />\n<br />\nUpdate: There\'s a <a href=\"http://www.pycs.net/bbum/2004/3/16/\">Mac OS X package</a> available for subversion 1.0.0. (via <a href=\"http://www.whump.com/moreLikeThis/link/03919\">Bill</a>)\n','Installing Subversion ...\n',0,0,'installing_subversion','2004-03-18 08:10:48',1,1);
